          <msContents>
            <summary>Manuscript is used for contemplation and study and is a medieval Hindu philosophical treatise and super-commentary on a commentary written by Śaṅkarācārya on the Taittirīyopaniṣad, exploring themes of the universal Self and its relationship to the underlying principles of existence such as the abstract concept of the brahman. Written from the perspective of the Advaita (non-dualism) Vedānta school of philosophy.</summary>
